{
  "answer": "**I was unable to locate a couplet by Mirza Ghalib matching the description of \"the heart being a piece of meat for the eyes' beak\" (or close variations like heart/flesh/meat with beak/talon/claw/nail/eye/glance/prey/falcon) in the English translation of *Diwan-e-Ghalib*.** \n\nThe corpus includes the full *Diwan-e-Ghalib* (239 ghazals),[^1] and I ran extensive searches on the English bodies for relevant phrases and keywords (e.g., \"heart meat eyes beak\", \"heart flesh eye\", \"meat heart\", \"beak\", \"heart eyes\", \"heart glance\"), but none matched in Ghalib's work.[^2] \"Beak\" appears only in unrelated texts like *Manusmṛti*.[^3]\n\nIt's possible the specific phrasing isn't used in this translation, the couplet uses different imagery, or it's not present in the corpus. If you have more details (e.g., a line in Urdu or radif/qafiya), I can search further.\n\n[^1]: *Diwan-E-Ghalib*, metadata overview (full work slug: mirza-ghalib-diwan-e-ghalib-74ed4c).\n[^2]: Multiple `search_corpus` results returned zero hits for Ghalib-related matches.\n[^3]: E.g., *Manusmṛti*, Chapter 5, [p-8f3656](https://falsafa.corpus/works/unknown-manusmrti-347b76/05/translation/#p-8f3656).",
